title: FS: Terrific Large 1899 Cabinet Photo with Harry Pattee from T206 (sold)
author: Jobu

posts.post_title: FS: Terrific Large 1899 Cabinet Photo with Harry Pattee from T206 (sold)
posts.post_content:
$375 net to me. SOLD

This photo is the 1899 Hillsboro team, which features a 17-year-old Harry Pattee of T206 fame (middle row in the dark sweater with XX on it). 

Great clarity and contrast. 

The mount is 15" x 12.5" and the photo itself is 9" x 7". It is impressive in person.
That's really neat! Do you know if Harry's outfit different because of his position, or some other reason?
Thanks! I wondered the same thing but I am not sure. It isn't because he is a sub because there is a sub listed, so maybe it is from a school team he was also on?
